data.title: Wave Life Sciences reported fourth quarter and full year 2025 financial results, having $602.1 million in cash equivalents, anticipating cash runway into 3Q 2028. INLIGHT trial expected in 1Q 2026, fat loss seen with WVE-007 similar to GLP-1, planning for Phase 2a. Regulatory engagement for WVE-006 on AATD, RestorAATion-2 trial fully enrolled, and CTA submission for WVE-008 for PNPLA3 liver disease. Revenue decrease from $108.3 million in 2024 to $42.7 million in 2025, with net loss of $204.4 million in 2025, compared to net income in the previous year.
data.description: Wave Life Sciences Ltd announced financial results for the fourth quarter and full year ended December 31, 2025, stating cash and cash equivalents of $602.1 million by that date, expected to fund operations into 3Q 2028. Notably, the INLIGHT clinical data update on WVE-007 showed fat loss similar to GLP-1 at three months, with muscle mass preservation; Phase 2a multidose trial for obesity planned for 1H 2026. WVE-006 for AATD showed successful AAT production and a potential accelerated approval pathway. Regulatory approval anticipated mid-2026. Another candidate, WVE-008 for PNPLA3 I148M liver disease, is on track for CTA submission in 2026. The company's revenue in 2025 was $42.7 million, with research and development expenses of $182.8 million and general and administrative expenses of $75.3 million. Net loss was $53.2 million for Q4 2025, contributing to a full-year 2025 loss of $204.4 million. Wave anticipates receiving milestone payments from their GSK collaboration and is focusing on RNA medicines to address various disorders. Major accomplishments of their pipeline include RNA editing for AATD, obesity treatment, and additional programs aimed at liver diseases. Furthermore, plans are in place for bringing DMD, GSK collaboration, and other initiatives to market. The company's financials are healthy, positioning them well for development and growth in the coming years.

data.title: EMCOR Group, Inc. reported Q4 2025 revenues of $4.51 billion, up 19.7% from Q4 2024, with net income of $434.6 million.
data.description: EMCOR Group, Inc. (NYSE: EME) announced its financial results for the fourth quarter and full year ending on December 31, 2025.
